node_Modules
1) This is a folder automatically created when you can run npm install (or yarn install/pnpm install).
2)It contains all the Installed dependencles (packages) your project needs. including React,Vite,ESline,and Third-party librarles.
3) Important : Never edit files inside it manually.and do not commit it to git
4)Public:- Folder for static files(Like images,favicon)that are served as-is.
5).gitignore:--> File that tells git which files /folder ignore(eg.node_modules).

Q. What is eslint.config.js?
`                             eslint.config.js is the configuration file for ESLine-a popular tool that analyzes your java script/Tyscript code for error..........

 ****=>eslint.config.js tells ESLine how to check your code and what rules to follow.

 1.package.json
 It acts like the identity card of your project.

 Q.What is contains:
    Project name,version,description.


2.Package-lock.json
It is an auto-generated fill created by npm.
It records the exact version of every package and sub-pakckage installed.
Why it exists.
To ensure everyone on the team gets the sane exatct versions of packages.

3.README.md
A markdown file that servers as the documentation for project.
Configuration fill for vite(build tool& dev server).

Q2. what is component in react ? types of component?
A component in react is a reusable(self-contained) piece of code that returns
 some piece of jsx.

 It is two types 
1.class Besed component(CBC)
 i).A class component is a JS class that extends React.compound.
 ii).it has render () ti return JSX.
 iii).it has the traditional and most popular way of writing React component before 2019.
2.Function based components(FBC)




